                        <condition>
                           <list>
                              <item>
                                 <p>Paper, about 5 7/8 in. by 4, consisting of 114 leaves, many of
                        which are much soiled and torn, especially foll. 1, 9, 11, 18, 36, 40—42,
                        50, 51, 55—60, 91—97, 100, 113, and 114. The quires, signed with letters,
                        are now 12 in number; but leaves are wanting after foll. 8, 10, 97, and 106,
                        as well as at the end. There are from 7 to 11 lines in each page.</p>
                              </item>
                           </list>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc hands="2">
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr">
                        <desc>The first eight leaves are written in a neat, regular hand of the
                              <date notBefore="1300" notAfter="1500">xivth or xvth cent.</date>, with many Greek and Syriac
                           vowels.</desc>
                     </handNote>
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr">
                <desc>The rest, though of the same date, are very badly written.</desc>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
                  <additions>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                           <locus/>
                           <p>On fol. 105 a, the scribe has recorded his name,
                                 <persName>Domitius</persName>.</p>
                           <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܨܠܘ ܥܠ ܕܝܡ̣ܛ ܚܛܝܐ ܘܠܲܠܐ ܘܣܲܟܠܐ ܘܦܲܛܥܐ ܘܓܥ̣ܝܛܐ ܘܓܥ̣ܝܨܐ ܕܣܪܛ܀</quote>
                  </p>
                        </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
